21 3. Has its headquarters or main campus physically located in Kentucky;
22 and
23 4. Does not qualify as a participating institution under KRS 164.7874(20);
24 (g) "Qualified proprietary school program" means a program offered by a
25 proprietary school that is in the field of agriculture as defined in KRS 246.010
26 or is in one (1) of Kentucky's top five (5) high-demand work sectors as
27 determined by the Kentucky Workforce Innovation Board;
