1 (h) "Qualified workforce training program" means a program that is in one (1) of
2 Kentucky's top five (5) high-demand work sectors as determined by the
3 Kentucky Workforce Innovation Board;
4 (i) "Registered apprenticeship program" means an apprenticeship program that:
5 1. Is established in accordance with the requirements of KRS Chapter 343;
6 2. Requires a minimum of two thousand (2,000) hours of on-the-job work
7 experience;
8 3. Requires a minimum of one hundred forty-four (144) hours of related
9 instruction for each year of the apprenticeship; and
10 4. Is approved by the Education and Labor Cabinet;
11 (j) "Related instruction" has the same meaning as in KRS 343.010; and
12 (k) "Sponsor" has the same meaning as in KRS 343.010.
13 (2) Notwithstanding KRS 164.7881, an eligible student who earned a KEES award
14 shall be eligible for a Kentucky educational excellence scholarship if the student
15 meets the requirements of this section and is:
16 (a) An apprentice in a registered apprenticeship program;
17 (b) Enrolled in a qualified workforce training program that has a current
18 articulation agreement for postsecondary credit hours with a participating
19 institution;
20 (c) Enrolled in a qualified proprietary school program;
21 (d) Enrolled in an approved workforce solutions training program; or
22 (e) Enrolled in an eligible college of art and design.
23 (3) (a) Beginning with the 2018-2019 academic year, an eligible student enrolled in a
24 registered apprenticeship program or, for the academic year beginning July 1,
25 2020, an eligible student enrolled in a qualified workforce training program
26 or, for the academic year beginning July 1, 2023, an eligible student enrolled
27 in a qualified proprietary school program, an approved workforce solutions
